Legal Calculus 4.5 — Enhanced Modules — Module 21
📘 Legal Calculus — Module 21

Extensions of Time — Good Cause & Diligence

⚖️ Core Message

Time is a rule. Ask early, show diligence, and propose a tight schedule.
📖 Lesson Content

1. Move before the deadline and show specific, case‑tied reasons.
2. Attach a brief declaration and a proposed order; offer a short, realistic new date.
3. Note prejudice to neither party and confirm conferral if required.
4. If denied, preserve timeliness and prejudice in a short notice.
📝 Assignment

Draft a 'Motion for Extension of Time' filed before the deadline with two concrete reasons and a 7‑day proposal.
✅ Model Response

MOTION FOR EXTENSION OF TIME

 

1. Plaintiff moves to extend the reply deadline by seven (7) days.

2. Good cause: (a) late‑served authority in Defendants’ Reply; (b) transcript delay.

3. Plaintiff proposes a new deadline of [date] and attaches a short order.

 

CERTIFICATE OF SERVICE

/s/ Charles Mayron

 

💡 Reflection Summary

Ask early, show diligence, and keep it short.
🎨 Visual Concept

A ticking clock with a small, approved extension tab.
